Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.88,0:01:40.70,Top,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's causing this.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.70,0:01:44.34,Top,,0,0,0,,Whenever I’m working out these equations, \Nmy eyelids simply drop.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.34,0:01:46.44,Top,,0,0,0,,It’s the eighth wonder of the world. {actually "one of the seven wonders"}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.81,0:01:47.58,Top,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.58,0:01:48.66,Top,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.66,0:01:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.71,0:01:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This young, love-struck Janet \Nkisses you in her dreams every night.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.52,0:01:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a trifle too forward?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.22,0:02:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, never mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.49,0:02:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.49,0:02:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's your deal, sneaking up on me?! {lit: what are you... suddenly}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.88,0:02:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a love letter?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.63,0:02:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom on earth?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.30,0:02:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's S-Secret!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.15,0:02:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Jimmy...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.67,0:02:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,From the circus!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.61,0:02:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiya!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I never guessed Janet would...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.30,0:02:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,write...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.16,0:02:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{love letters }to Jimmy!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.39,0:02:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been sending him \Ndozens upon dozens of letters? {so far}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.69,0:02:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So what if I have? {/what's it to you/got a complaint?}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.05,0:02:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And has he ever answered?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.10,0:02:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,An answer? How rude to ask!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.27,0:02:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To expect an answer would be indelicate. {impure; adulterated; foul; mixed; dishonest - probably means "crude/vulgar" as in "a decent lady wouldn't do that"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.12,0:02:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Jimmy being lodged \Nin my heart is enough for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.17,0:02:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.89,0:02:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got any letters for me today?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That answers it. {? lit: this is it, the thing - probably mean "look how eager she is despite saying that would be indelicate"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.32,0:03:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve already sent a dozen.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.86,0:03:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He could've written at least once in return.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.33,0:03:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy does travel a lot, doesn’t he?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.46,0:03:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the letters never reached him.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.87,0:03:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perchance...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.33,0:03:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he was taken ill?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.40,0:03:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.37,0:03:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re anxious, you should have Margot of the fifth form read your fortune.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.97,0:03:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.88,0:03:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They say she’s a dab hand at the tarot. \NHer divining is frightfully accurate.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.05,0:03:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the rage in the fifth form just now! {episode title}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.68,0:03:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Tarot fortune-telling?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.20,0:03:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tarot cards harbour a curious magic.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.34,0:03:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That magic,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.24,0:04:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reader’s gift, \Nmay pierce present, past, and future.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.11,0:04:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot even foretold \NPamela’s sister’s marriage to the letter.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.19,0:04:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, Janet, I will divine whether a reply will come from this youth called Jimmy.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.54,0:04:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.98,0:04:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This card represents his present.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.83,0:04:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The present?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.41,0:04:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest easy; he is hale and hearty.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.37,0:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... How relieving!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.06,0:04:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.58,0:04:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? He's a gentle sort of lad, is he not?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.58,0:05:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Indeed he is!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.04,0:05:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Blimey! How did you know that?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.31,0:05:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... {meaning "oh, I understand now" - not directly answering isabel}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.61,0:05:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Did you understand something?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.10,0:05:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, you have waited so long for his reply, have you not?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.72,0:05:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been hard for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.57,0:05:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! It really has.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.99,0:05:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So... will an answer come?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.55,0:05:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be impatient.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.24,0:05:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What does it mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.61,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, the cards show no reply will come.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.78,0:05:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.08,0:05:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell me the letters have not been received.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.27,0:05:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh no...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.53,0:06:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.78,0:06:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But do not be downcast, Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.83,0:06:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Look here.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.20,0:06:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see a token of good fortune very near at hand.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.88,0:06:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A token of good fortune?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.01,0:06:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Some small windfall \Nmay all at once befall you. {/piece of luck }
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.97,0:06:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.48,0:06:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A sudden windfall? {/bit of luck}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.01,0:06:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds a tad suspicious, doesn’t it? \NI don’t much trust these fortunes, to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.08,0:06:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.30,0:06:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because whatever they say to you \Nis always the fancy stuff you want to believe. {? unsure, maybe "is always the fancy stuff that's guaranteed to be true"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.34,0:06:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"He's a gentle sort of lad, is he not?"
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yes! Indeed he is."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.31,0:06:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"He is hale and hearty."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.40,0:06:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"How relieving!"
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.71,0:06:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But it did indeed seem \Nlike things worked out well today. {??? no idea what's that matoeta}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.75,0:06:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.10,0:07:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.79,0:07:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A sudden windfall!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.56,0:07:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What, really? \NJanet, do you seriously believe it?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.10,0:07:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Janet here?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.05,0:07:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.30,0:07:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked the lending card, you see.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.14,0:07:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you borrow this book half a year ago?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.36,0:07:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside it, with your report, \Nyou forgot your pocket-money.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.87,0:07:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was lost for good!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.81,0:07:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Ten shillings!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.68,0:07:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurrah! What luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.88,0:07:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It came true...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.35,0:07:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My sudden windfall!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.66,0:07:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No mistake—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.81,0:07:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the fortune was right!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.53,0:07:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraordinary!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.31,0:07:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m bound to believe it now!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.25,0:07:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.87,0:07:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do teach me how to read the tarot!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.33,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I long to work miracles \Nwith fortune-telling too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.32,0:07:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.10,0:08:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you make of it, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.18,0:08:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.73,0:08:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Could Janet’s ten-shilling miracle be genuine?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.69,0:08:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Codswallop! She only blundered six months ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.14,0:08:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where’s the miracle in that?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.09,0:08:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.38,0:08:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.58,0:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.88,0:08:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet’s begun telling fortunes?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.03,0:08:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, bother!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.96,0:08:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I ought to have charged a shilling a head, \Nseeing how it’s thriving. {/per person}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.90,0:08:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re only in it for the lark. {/for fun; half in jest}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.75,0:08:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll never prove true anyway...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.22,0:08:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Not with our blundering Janet! {/absent-minded - probably referring to her forgetting her 10 shillings in the book }
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.11,0:09:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Behold the powers of Janet the Great Seeress!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.31,0:09:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, Sheila Naylor, \Nyour present is...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.65,0:09:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.65,0:09:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.62,0:09:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, you’ve a bit of a cold \Njust now, haven’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.14,0:09:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.56,0:09:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.66,0:09:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you were coughing this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.86,0:09:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone could tell.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.70,0:09:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.04,0:09:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.24,0:09:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.24,0:09:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.96,0:09:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone’s in love with Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.14,0:09:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,T...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.28,0:09:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.45,0:09:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Madly.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.43,0:09:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.95,0:09:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now... Isn’t it John of the stationer’s? {probably means "the son of stationery shop owner"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.32,0:09:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, when you bought an eraser, \Nhe gave you such a smile.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.11,0:09:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, John? Oh no...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.30,0:09:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t mean it!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.67,0:10:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That handsome John... \NWhatever shall I do!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A yellow ribbon will be \Nyour lucky token in love. {lucky chance}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.34,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A yellow ribbon?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.30,0:10:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.40,0:10:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.91,0:10:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! Whatever shall I do!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.05,0:10:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at her after saying it'll never prove true! {lit: despite her saying ... - referring to 8:53}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.37,0:10:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it does look rather fun. \NDivine for me next!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.43,0:10:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.33,0:10:26.09,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.09,0:10:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.89,0:10:27.99,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.63,0:10:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.60,0:10:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.40,0:10:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s dreadful!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.61,0:10:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Janet’s divination, \Nsomething unexpected is to befall us today!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.35,0:10:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From early this morning I’ve had the feeling—\Nan unexpected happening is certain!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.22,0:10:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes true, I may begin to believe \Nin Janet’s divination.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.45,0:10:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So shall I.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.94,0:10:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,An unexpected happening... \NIt’s bound to come!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.43,0:11:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.86,0:11:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.41,0:11:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're having a busy morning, girls.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.86,0:11:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.24,0:11:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.21,0:11:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of late I’ve had the impression \Nthat your minds have been curiously unsettled.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.51,0:11:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it only my fancy?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.88,0:11:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To sharpen your wits, \NI shall set you a surprise test.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.49,0:11:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.94,0:11:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.26,0:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s happened!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.53,0:11:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The sudden unexpected thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.01,0:11:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Janet’s cards, I’m “Red.” {??? "aka"}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.18,0:11:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m “A.” {??? still dunno what this is about}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.16,0:11:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"A?" Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.28,0:11:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.58,0:12:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, shall we all go to the pictures? \NThat new one everyone’s talking about. {/the hot topic}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.42,0:12:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pictures?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.25,0:12:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.96,0:12:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m too busy with my knitting.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.56,0:12:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet’s divination says \Na red jumper will bring me luck! {/sweater}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.43,0:12:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I’d rather read.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.80,0:12:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She said any book with a title beginning with “A” will improve my marks in tests this month!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:12.93,0:12:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up! Are you people serious?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.83,0:12:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say everyone’s taken in \Nby Janet’s divining?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.42,0:12:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But she did hit the nail on the head! \NThat surprise maths test.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.64,0:12:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? It was incredible!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.18,0:12:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure chance!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.34,0:12:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I’m far too busy.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.31,0:12:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.20,0:12:36.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,Extraordinary! \NSomeone’s in love with Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.56,0:12:39.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Could it be John, the stationer’s son?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.36,0:12:42.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,A yellow ribbon is your lucky token in love.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.50,0:12:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Young lady, what a pretty ribbon you have!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.23,0:12:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don’t! It’s far too embarrassing!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.03,0:13:02.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I swear... This fortune-telling craze... \NEveryone’s gone clean daft!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.00,0:13:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet says I mustn’t marry \Ntill I’m twenty-eight. I’m shattered!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.52,0:13:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She says I’ll never be a nurse!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.79,0:13:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my dream, \Nbut I suppose I must give it up.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.36,0:13:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it up? Nonsense! \NIf you long to be a nurse, then work for it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.80,0:13:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.60,0:13:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, marry at twenty \Nif you please, and be happy!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.74,0:13:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn’t let fortunes rule you—never!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.67,0:13:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we O’Sullivan twins \Nwon’t be taken in by such rubbish!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.14,0:13:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel! \NLet’s go to the pictures.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.93,0:13:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But, Pat, listen.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.11,0:13:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve just been told—the destiny of twins \Nis governed by the same star.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.89,0:13:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.69,0:13:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t mean to say even you think people’s fates \Nare settled by a pack of cards now?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.26,0:13:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But... I do feel there’s something to it. {/mysterious power}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.93,0:13:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps people’s lives are mapped out \Nfrom the moment they’re born?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.87,0:13:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.70,0:14:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The fates of St. Clare’s first-formers \Nare all revealed by Janet’s cards!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.93,0:14:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet! You're seriously getting ahead of yourself! {lit: riding the impulse - means she's getting overconfident and overbearing}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.15,0:14:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing the oracle\N and leading everyone a dance! {think she means "you think it's fun to mislead everyone?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.40,0:14:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.82,0:14:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You braggart! {/conceited person}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.54,0:14:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You stubborn mule! {/obstinate\Nperson}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That settles it—our friendship’s over!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.36,0:14:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.38,0:14:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You two...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.06,0:14:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll bring a terrible punishment on yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.40,0:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well! Try it, then. \NPunishment or whatever you please!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.24,0:14:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell my fortune, if you dare.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.07,0:14:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it proves false, \Nthen it shows you’re an impostor.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.94,0:14:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it comes true?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.58,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I’ll obey you all my life.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.98,0:15:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray, tell us Patricia O’Sullivan’s fate.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.00,0:15:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What shall befall her within three days?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.32,0:15:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.82,0:15:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.79,0:15:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Something dreadful!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.29,0:15:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A misfortune is to come upon Pat. \NWithin three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.96,0:15:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What kind of misfortune?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.03,0:15:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t tell... \NA sinister accident...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.34,0:15:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A curse!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.79,0:15:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? A curse?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.58,0:15:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, within three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.11,0:15:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh! No need to remind Pat. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.96,0:15:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.95,0:15:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.79,0:15:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, with all the... {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.64,0:16:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What curse? It’s nonsense!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.30,0:16:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.27,0:16:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But the whole school’s buzzing with it! \NPoor Patricia O’Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.06,0:16:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They say she may die!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.94,0:16:16.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,Really, why do they need to say things like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.68,0:16:24.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,“Misfortune” my butt!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.42,0:16:26.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,But... Suppose...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.61,0:16:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who’s there?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.74,0:16:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh... It’s just you, Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.66,0:16:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Today...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.72,0:16:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the third day.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.02,0:17:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if only she could be safe past twelve o’clock!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.74,0:17:20.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,One more hour and Janet’s prophecy \Nwill be done with. {lit: the predicted 3 days will be over}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.56,0:17:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To the lavatory, I suppose. \NShe’d be safer if she stayed still.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.63,0:17:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Not that we're tagging after you \Nout of worry, mind you!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.99,0:17:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.94,0:17:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,L-Look there!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.12,0:17:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.27,0:17:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavens! The stables!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.98,0:18:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.75,0:18:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was me who brought the misfortune! \NWhat am I to do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.37,0:18:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The horses! They’ll die!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.86,0:18:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.99,0:18:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.83,0:18:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.48,0:18:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, the curse still looms over you!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.28,0:18:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.10,0:18:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Blazes! I must tell the mistresses! {???? sensei sounds awful lot like "penpen/pinpin" here}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.64,0:18:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll let you go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.99,0:18:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Run quickly!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.14,0:18:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.96,0:18:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there, you'll be all right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.98,0:18:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.57,0:18:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat and Janet are inside!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.52,0:18:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.57,0:18:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.73,0:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.59,0:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.50,0:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, quick!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.98,0:18:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.04,0:18:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.94,0:18:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.20,0:18:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.01,0:19:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.81,0:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.85,0:19:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher! Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.66,0:19:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My students are in there!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.17,0:19:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll handle this.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.89,0:19:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.96,0:19:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.97,0:19:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.92,0:19:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.21,0:19:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.44,0:19:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.88,0:19:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, did you seriously think I’d die?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.15,0:19:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.85,0:19:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.90,0:19:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.49,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.39,0:19:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Injuries?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.02,0:19:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,None!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.39,0:19:53.54,Overlap,,0,0,0,,None at all! {? think both are arimasen}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.03,0:19:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprised? Pat’s indestructible!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.67,0:20:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And Janet too!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.93,0:20:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No—Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.84,0:20:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your quick action, \Nthe stable only partially burned.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.45,0:20:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the horses are safe, \Nall thanks to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.07,0:20:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.50,0:20:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Pat, too much bravery \Ncan land you in hot water. {/is troublesome}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.49,0:20:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If something like this happens again, \Ndon’t take such dangerous action.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.15,0:20:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.68,0:20:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I must commend \Nyour wonderful teamwork.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.74,0:20:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve decided to award you a special show \Nat the next school assembly. {?? dunno what's that "school meeting"}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.52,0:20:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.88,0:20:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A show?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.48,0:20:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And Janet...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.98,0:20:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.45,0:20:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This arrived for you this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.15,0:20:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.92,0:20:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.06,0:21:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.63,0:21:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Exchanging letters with boys is forbidden.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.13,0:21:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But this one is probably from a girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.37,0:21:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.12,0:21:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Janet, I’ve been too busy to reply, \Nbut I read your every letter.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.84,0:21:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a token of thanks."
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.10,0:21:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.33,0:21:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Far from misfortune...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.57,0:21:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s the greatest happiness!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.47,0:21:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps that great misfortune \Nwas that our friendship nearly broke?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.14,0:21:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.08,0:21:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Fate can be changed by your own efforts.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.25,0:21:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Achieved through effort.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.09,0:22:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, aren’t you getting tired of fortune-telling?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.36,0:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortune-telling? That’s old news.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.93,0:22:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, it’s all about charms.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.73,0:22:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.56,0:22:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray for Jimmy!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.60,0:22:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray for youth!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.38,0:23:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary’s father fell ill.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.45,0:23:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation was successful \Nand his life was saved...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.38,0:23:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but he had to give up the school he ran.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.79,0:23:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.73,0:23:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And what, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.03,0:23:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary can no longer pay her tuition fees,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.85,0:23:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so she must leave St. Clare’s!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.85,0:23:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.87,0:23:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary leaving St. Clare’s—\Nsurely that’s impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.27,0:23:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.87,0:24:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"Don’t Leave, Hilary!" {やめないで、ヒラリー!}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.29,0:24:03.76,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 19\NDon’t Leave, Hilary! {やめないで、ヒラリー!}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.47,0:24:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
